# NOTES

	- evm/setup (execute with ./setup) creates a fully compatible evm node given the same genesis.json file
	- resetting the blockchain (evm) is as simple as rm -rf node/data/geth*
	- node_1 and node_3 are on (vds_1 and vds_2)
	- screen -ls shows what is running: manager (on node_1) is the experimental all in one manager for both instances
	- remember to sh attach.sh to work inside kyntainers

# PROJECT RECAP

	- clean.sh -> remove and clean image for kyntainer
	- deploy.sh -> build the image, create and run the kyntainer give the dockerfile
	- run.sh -> run the kyntainer (here are defined the volumes too)
	- stop.sh -> stop the kyntainer
	- cleanbuild.sh -> remove and clean image for kynainer then build (but not run) the image again
	- attach.sh -> attach to the kyntainer
	- name -> contains and defines the kyntainer docker container name
	- env_setup.sh -> is not working, in run.sh everything is defined there
	- evm/setup -> see above
	- evm/clean.sh -> rm -rf node/data/geth* and rebuild the genesis block with the genesis.json file
	- evm/run.sh -> geth run with options
	- requirements -> files used and copied in the Dockerfile (such as geth)
	- demos/ -> all the demos files
	- common/ -> files used for both evm and demos layers (such as manager.js)
